cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the reconstruction of face images. The use of a progressive training method and attention loss also suggests that it may fall under the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed compressed version of the face alignment network (FAN) may indicate that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Lastly, the focus on facial attributes and details may suggest that it could also fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
